    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "document",
        "modelId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "models/gemini-2.5-flash",
          "mode": "list",
          "cachedResultName": "models/gemini-2.5-flash"
        },
        "text": "=Target Jurisdiction: {{ $('⚙️ REGION CONFIGURATION').item.json.Target_Jurisdiction }}\n\nFirst, classify the document. If it is NOT a Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, or Data Processing Agreement (e.g., invoices, user manuals), set \"Applicable\": false.\n\nAudit the text for Automated Decision-Making (ADM) and AI profiling compliance strictly under the specified Target Jurisdiction:\n- If \"US\": Audit against CCPA/CPRA rules (ADM logic transparency, opt-out rights).\n- If \"Canada\": Audit against CPPA / Bill C-27 rules (algorithmic transparency, right to explanation).\n- If \"AUS\": Audit against Privacy Act Reform rules (mandatory disclosure for automated decisions).\n- If \"Global\": Audit against all three frameworks.\n\nOutput strictly valid JSON with these exact keys:\n{\n  \"Applicable\": true/false,\n  \"Document_Type\": \"Privacy Policy / Terms of Service / Unrelated\",\n  \"Target_Jurisdiction\": \"{{ $('⚙️ REGION CONFIGURATION').item.json.Target_Jurisdiction }}\",\n  \"Risk_Level\": \"High / Medium / Low / N/A\",\n  \"Missing_Clauses\": \"[Specific missing legal clauses strictly for the target region]\",\n  \"Existing_Deficient_Text\": \"[Extract the exact verbatim sentence from the text that mentions automated processing, algorithms, or profiling without providing the legally required disclosures/opt-outs. Do not return 'Not found'. If they lack ADM mentions entirely, extract their broadest data collection or personalization clause.]\",\n  \"Action_Required\": \"[1-2 sentence concrete remediation step]\"\n}\n\nText to analyze:\n{{ $json.text }}",
        "inputType": "binary",
        "binaryPropertyName": "=data",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.googleGemini",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        240,
        592
      ],
